cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CE

The paper discusses the application of massive MIMO technology to IoT connectivity, which involves wireless communication and network protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory), which deals with the mathematical foundations of communication and information processing. The paper also discusses the challenges and opportunities of integrating massive MIMO with IoT, which suggests that it could belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes communication schemes and discusses network slicing, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
